      "sc:description": "Virus-host codon usage co-adaptation analysis.\n\nAnalyze the co-adaptation of codon usage between a virus and its host, calculate various codon usage bias measurements as: effective number of codons (ENc) Novembre (2002) <doi:10.1093 oxfordjournals.molbev.a004201>, codon adaptation index (CAI) Sharp and Li (1987) <doi:10.1093 nar 15.3.1281>, relative codon deoptimization index (RCDI) Puigb√≤ et al (2010) <doi:10.1186 1756-0500-3-87>, similarity index (SiD) Zhou et al (2013) <doi:10.1371 journal.pone. 0077239>, synonymous codon usage orderliness (SCUO) Wan et al (2004) <doi:10.1186 1471-2148-4-19> and, relative synonymous codon usage (RSCU) Sharp et al (1986) <doi:10.1093 nar 14.13.5125>.\n\nvhcub is an R package to analyze the co-adaptation of codon usage between a virus and its host.\n\nFurthermore, vhcub uses ggplot to visualize two important plots named ENc-GC3 plot and PR2plot, which help to explain what are the factors influence a virus's evolution concerning its CUB",
